      "title": "Can the stockmarket swallow Anthropic, SpaceX and OpenAI?",
      "url": "https://www.economist.com/finance-and-economics/2026/06/01/can-the-stockmarket-swallow-anthropic-spacex-and-openai",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48364055",
      "score": 667,
      "comments": 1140,
      "author": "1vuio0pswjnm7",
      "published": "2026-06-01T23:45:46Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Mega-cap AI startups like OpenAI ($150B) and Anthropic ($40B) require massive public market liquidity to sustain escalating compute and training costs.",
        "Traditional venture capital cannot support multi-billion-dollar compute scaling laws; IPOs are necessary to fund next-generation frontier AI infrastructure.",
        "Transitioning to public markets will force foundation model vendors to prove real enterprise software margins over speculative private valuations."
      ]
    },
