      "bullets": [
        "GitHub centralizes git, replacing decentralized version control with proprietary APIs, non-portable Pull Requests, and vendor-locked issues.",
        "GitHub Actions fosters vendor lock-in with proprietary runner environments and YAML formats, hindering multi-cloud and hybrid-cloud DevOps portability.",
        "DevOps teams should evaluate open, self-hosted, or federated Git alternatives like GitLab, Forgejo, or Sourcehut to mitigate single-provider dependency."
      ]
